<p>I am trying to run a <strong>Flask</strong> application with Apache by using <code>mod_wsgi</code> on <strong>CentOS7</strong>.</p>  <p>The application path is: <code>/var/www/my_app</code></p>  <p>The project is configured by using a <strong>Python Virtual Environment</strong>, preciselly, there is a subfolder <code>/var/www/my_app/proj_env/</code> that contains all the env files.</p>  <p>The <code>/var/www/my_app/wsgi.py</code> is:</p>  <pre><code>from main import app as application </code></pre>  <p>Then, the virtual host is configured as follows:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;      ServerName my_app.mydom.com      &lt;Directory /var/www/my_app&gt;         &lt;Files wsgi.py&gt;             Require all granted         &lt;/Files&gt;     &lt;/Directory&gt;      WSGIDaemonProcess my_app python-path=/var/www/my_app:/var/www/my_app/proj_env/lib/python2.7/site-packages     WSGIProcessGroup my_app     WSGIScriptAlias / /var/www/my_app/wsgi.py  &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Unfortunately, when I try to start apache, the system returns me an error,</p>  <pre><code>Oct 02 17:17:58  systemd[1]: httpd.service: control process exited, code=exited status=1 Oct 02 17:17:58 systemd[1]: Failed to start The Apache HTTP Server. </code></pre>  <p>What am I doing wrong?</p>